  "title" : "ant - JAVA_HOME is not defined correctly",
  "body" : "<p>I have installed java with the command sudo apt-get install openjdk-7-jdk and set the java home and path.But when I am trying to use ant I </p>\n\n<pre><code>JAVA_HOME is not defined correctly.\n  We cannot execute /usr/local/java/jre1.7.0_60/bin/java\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Please help me how to resolve this error.</p>\n\n<pre><code>which java   ----&gt; /usr/bin/java\njava -version ----&gt;java version \"1.6.0_31\"\nOpenJDK Runtime Environment (IcedTea6 1.13.3) (6b31-1.13.3-1ubuntu1~0.12.04.2)\nOpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 23.25-b01, mixed mode)\n\necho $JAVA_HOME  -----&gt;  /usr/local/java/jre1.7.0_60\n</code></pre>\n"
